MOTORISTS have been advised  to avoid the M19 towards Durban due to protest action. According to Arrive Alive traffic has been affected, as protesters blocked the road with burning tyres. "The public is urged to avoid the area of the M19 near Clare Road as violent protest action has erupted. Public order policing are in attendance. "The M19 is closed to traffic heading towards the city, motorists are urged to use alternative routes,"  Marshall Security's Kyle van Reenen said. He said it is believed the protest is over the demolition of informal shacks in the area. 